        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4 col-md-3">
            <div class="ripple grey team boxed-grey">
                <div class="inner">
                    <h5>Safe Zones</h5>
                    <p class="subtitle">Safe Zones are areas in which you cannot eliminate or be eliminated by anyone. Safe zones include:</p>
                    <ul class="rules">
                        <li><strong>Cabell and Tompkins-McCaw Library</strong></li>
                        <li><strong>Cary Street Gym</strong></li>
                        <li><strong>Shafer (both floors)</strong></li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="subtitle">The following places have 15 minute grace period BEFORE and AFTER:</p>
                    <ul class="rules">
                        <li><strong>CSA events</strong> (and 15 minutes before and after them)</li>
                        <li><strong><a style="padding:0px;" href="http://goo.gl/zmfRZ8" target="_blank">CSA Culture Show practices</a></strong></li>
                        <li><strong>Classes</strong></li>
                        <li><strong>Workplaces</strong></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4 col-md-3">
            <div class="ripple grey team boxed-grey">
                <div class="inner">
                    <h5>Reporting Eliminations</h5>
                    <p class="subtitle">When you eliminate someone, report it right away. You must post a picture with you, your weapon, and your dead target to the CSA Assassin Facebook page AND this website. For this site, click on your profile in the menu. There will be a "Confirm a Kill" button. Report your kill as soon as possible to keep the game running smoothly.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ripple grey team boxed-grey">
                <div class="inner">
                    <h5>Outside Assistance</h5>
                    <p class="subtitle">No one is allowed to eliminate your target but you. They may help you find a target but they CANNOT physically do anything to help you. Examples include but not limited to, holding the target from running, blocking the target’s way, closing doors on them etc. Only you should be physically touching your target.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
